### NextDev API — HTTP Request Collection
### Use with VS Code "REST Client" extension or IntelliJ HTTP Client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000/api/v1
@token = PASTE_TOKEN_HERE_AFTER_LOGIN

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Accept: application/json

### Register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Smith",
  "username": "janesmith",
  "email": "jane@example.com",
  "password": "Password1!",
  "password_confirmation": "Password1!",
  "locale": "en"
}

### Check username availability
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/check-username?username=janesmith
Accept: application/json

### Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "email": "dev@nextdev.io",
  "password": "Password1!",
  "remember": false,
  "device_name": "REST Client"
}

### Get current user (requires token from login/register response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Logout (current device)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "all_devices": false
}

### Logout (all devices)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "all_devices": true
}

### Forgot password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "email": "dev@nextdev.io"
}

### Reset password (token comes from the email link / mail log in local dev)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "token": "PASTE_RESET_TOKEN_HERE",
  "email": "dev@nextdev.io",
  "password": "NewPassword1!",
  "password_confirmation": "NewPassword1!"
}

### Validation error example — duplicate email
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "Test",
  "username": "testuser2",
  "email": "dev@nextdev.io",
  "password": "Password1!",
  "password_confirmation": "Password1!"
}

### Validation error example — reserved username
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "Test",
  "username": "admin",
  "email": "newuser@example.com",
  "password": "Password1!",
  "password_confirmation": "Password1!"
}
